# Copy to `.env` in this folder (or use `mobile/SwapJoy/.env` for Expo-only vars).
# Never commit `.env` — it is gitignored.
#
# Postgres URI (for scripts / psql / Prisma — not the Expo app):
# 1. Open your project: https://supabase.com/dashboard/project/_/database/settings
# 2. Click the green "Connect" button at the top of the dashboard (not always under Settings).
# 3. Pick a method, then copy the URI:
#    - Direct: IPv6 only on many networks — if DNS fails (ENOTFOUND), avoid this.
#    - Session pooler: good for IPv4 + tools like pg / one-off scripts.
#    - Transaction pooler: port 6543; some clients need "disable prepared statements".
# Docs: https://supabase.com/docs/guides/database/connecting-to-postgres
#
# Paste the copied string below (replace [YOUR-PASSWORD] if the UI shows a placeholder).
DATABASE_URL=

# Optional: scripts like `scripts/generate-pexels-item-images-migration.mjs`
PEXELS_API_KEY=
